                          <item xml:id="a4">
                            <desc type="Condemnation">Condemnation against those who steal or erase the book. The note is written over erasure and the names of the individuals have been erased again</desc>
                              <locus target="#157va">Fol. 157va</locus>
                            <q xml:lang="gez">ዝመጽሐፍ፡ … ዘተሣየጦ፡ በንዋዮ፡ … ለመድኃኒተ፡ ነፍስ፡ ወሥጋ፡ ባሕ ቱ፡ ዘሰረቆ፡ ወዘፈሐቆ፡ ወተአገሎ፡ በአፈ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ወም ቱረ፡ ለይኩን፡ ለይኩን፡</q>
                          </item>
                            <item xml:id="a5"><desc type="GuestText"><ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3058RepCh338">Ǝsäggǝd läki ǝsäggǝd läki ǝsäggǝd läki wäʾǝweddǝsäki</ref> (“I worship you, I worship you, I worship you and I praise you”, Hymn to the Virgin Mary, Chaine nr. 338). The hymn is written in an inaccurate hand. The refrain of each stanza is rubricated. Incipit:</desc> 
                              <locus from="157vb" to="158vb">Fols 157vb–158vb</locus>
                              <q xml:lang="gez">[እ]ሰግድ፡ ለኪ፡ ወ[እ]ዌድስኪ፡ ኦእ ግዝእትየ፡ ቅድስት፡ ድንግል፡ ማርያም፡ ወላዲተ፡ አምላክ፡ በከመ፡ ወደሱኪ፡ ወሰገዱ፡ ለኪ፡ መላእክት፡</q>
